## Centering a Div

There are several ways to center a div, depending on your needs:

---

### Horizontally Center (Block Element)
```css
div {
  width: 200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}
```

---

### Flexbox (Most Common/Recommended)
```css
.parent {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center; /* horizontal */
  align-items: center;     /* vertical */
  height: 100vh;           /* needed for vertical centering */
}
```

---

### CSS Grid
```css
.parent {
  display: grid;
  place-items: center;
  height: 100vh;
}
```

---

### Absolute Positioning
```css
.parent {
  position: relative;
}

.child {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
}
```

---

### Quick Comparison

| Method | Horizontal | Vertical | Notes |
|--------|-----------|----------|-------|
| `margin: auto` | ‚úÖ | ‚ùå | Needs a set width |
| Flexbox | ‚úÖ | ‚úÖ | Best for most cases |
| Grid | ‚úÖ | ‚úÖ | Great for layouts |
| Absolute | ‚úÖ | ‚úÖ | Needs relative parent |

---

**Flexbox** is generally the most recommended modern approach for its simplicity and flexibility.
